We recommended the following:

After appraisal of the parcels of land, the result will be the basis for the Office of the Municipal Accountant in the recording of the same in the books of accounts; 

The Office of the Municipal Accountant to observe Section 63 of PD No. 1445 and Paragraphs 26 and 27 of the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards 17 on the proper measurement on the recognition of the parcels of land and make the necessary correcting/adjusting entries;

We recommended that the LCE direct the responsible/concerned department heads to do the following (based on the guidelines prescribed by COA Circular No. 2018-002):

1. Secure directly from the GSIS GIF the GSIS GIF all insurances or bonds covering properties, contracts, rights of action and other insurable risks of their respective offices;

2. Prepare the Property Inventory Form (PIF) listing of the insurable properties and other assets, showing their latest appraised values/valuation, appraised date, location, and other information;

3. Extract from the Report on the Physical Count of PPE the data for the PIF pertaining to the insurable assets and interest of the government;

4. Cause the appraisal of the insurable properties and other assets of their respective offices;

5. Submit the consolidated PIF to the Office of the Auditor and the GIF, GSIS not later than April 30 of each year; 

6. Include in the annual appropriation the amount of premiums for the general insurance covering all insurable assets and other assets and ensure its payment to the GSIS; and

7. Ensure centralized payment of insurance premiums to avoid double payment.

