We recommended that the LCE direct the:

LDRRM Officer and Other Persons Responsible to:

Ensure that the budget for the LDRRM Office be adequately provided including administrative expenses and capital outlay and use the fund prudently;
Avoid charging non-allowable expenses against the LDRRM Fund in order to avoid audit suspensions/disallowances;
Submit all the DVs for expenses charged against the LDRRMF. Audit suspensions or disallowances will be issued if none is submitted; and
Submit the lacking supporting documents of the submitted DVs. Audit suspensions or disallowances will be issued if none is submitted.

MHO and other personnel concerned to refund the excess hazard pay received for CY 2016 and comply strictly with rules and regulations stated in the Revised IRR of RA No. 7305 and DBM-DOH Joint Circular No. 1, S. 2012;

Municipal Accountant to check the accuracy of the payment and completeness of the required supporting documents and correctness of the amount to be paid;

Municipal Treasurer to double check the payroll submitted and see to it that the claims are correct; and

Municipal Treasurer and MHO to make sure that everything is in order before certifying in the Obligation Request that the charges to appropriation/allotment are necessary, lawful and under his/her direct supervision and supporting documents are valid, proper and legal.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed that the Local Chief Executive direct the following:
Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of all its properties and prepare and submit the RPCPPE for all types of PPE;
The Municipal Accountant and the GSO reconcile their respective PPE records;
The Municipal Accountant and the GSO maintain the required PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards respectively; and
The Municipality avail of the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts as provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006 to finally establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition, and accountability.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed that the Local Chief Executive direct the following:
HRMO, together with all other Department Heads, to spearhead the drafting of the internal policy regarding the hiring of the job order personnel. The policy must include the basis of rates on a daily wage or piecework basis pursuant to Sec. 77 of RA 7160 and CSC Resolution No. 020790, and monitoring of the services rendered by the JO personnel among others;
HRMO, with the aid of all other Department Heads, to maintain a database of all JO personnel hired for monitoring purposes;
HRMO and OIC-Municipal Accountant to require the persons hired as JOs and COS to submit Accomplishment Reports and attach it to the corresponding Liquidation Reports;
Comply with the requirements set in hiring of JOs and COS provided in Section 77 of the RA No. 7160 and CSC in its Resolution No. 020790; and
Submit to the office of the auditor the Memorandum of Agreement between the LGU of Estancia and KALAHI for the Contract of Service counterpart.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed to the following:
Re-visit the Municipal Ordinance No. 16 Series of 2005 and update the rules and regulations as well as the fines imposed for each violation to suit the current situation, if necessary;
Have a dialogue with the barangay and educate the barangay officials and employees on their responsibilities in ensuring that their constituents abide by the rules and regulations provided in RA No. 9003;
Conduct effective Information and Education Campaign in the entire municipality most especially in the barangays where garbage and wastes are not well managed, of the prohibited acts and the corresponding fines and penalties of those who will be caught violating said rules; and
Strictly impose the prescribed fines and penalties on individuals or establishments who will continue to leave or throw waste in public places.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed that the Local Chief Executive together with the responsible officials and employees do the following:
Update or Create the new Municipal Solid Waste Management Board based on Section 12 of the RA No. 9003;
Establish Material Recovery Facilities in the barangays and require the Barangay Officials and Employees to be responsible in the maintenance and operation of the MRF;
Provide a set of properly marked containers as “compostable”, “non-recyclable”, “recyclable” or “special waste” for on-site collection to avoid or minimize littering of waste in public places; and
Strictly impose the No Segregation No Collection Policy in the municipality.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed to the following:
Official/employee assigned to control and approve the DTTs to see to it that all data needed be accomplished, such as the fuel balances and consumption, distance travelled, purpose of travel and vehicle plate number;
Designated drivers to request their passenger(s) to affix their signatures in the approved DTTs after the trip;
Duly accomplished Monthly Report of Official Travels and Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption be submitted to COA Office; and
The management to stop the practice of providing fuel, oil and lubricants to private vehicles or those which do not bear government plates.

